523
00:25:42,090 --> 00:25:43,680
On the other hand, for clean backups,

524
00:25:43,680 --> 00:25:47,160
you can safely move them
to an isolated environment

525
00:25:47,160 --> 00:25:49,530
to ensure that you always restore

526
00:25:49,530 --> 00:25:53,160
from these isolated
logically air-gapped vaults

527
00:25:53,160 --> 00:25:56,253
to make sure that the backups
you're restoring is safe.

528
00:25:57,330 --> 00:25:58,950
How it looks on the console?

